    <!--I think the most effective way is the regulations released by the government. Firstly, through the
    enforcement of the law, the environment would be improved during a short period. For e.g. if the government
    prohibits the use of private cars, no one will dare to drive , because if they violate the law ,they would have
    to pay high price, the air quality would be greatly enhanced. While, environment protection organizations have
    relatively limited power, so the businesses would ignore their voice; as for individuals, they are often
    self-serving, and not able to discipline themselves if they get some benefits from doing things that are
    actually hurting the environment.-->

    <!--Games perform multiple functions for adults and of course are very important. Firstly, playing games is a
    kind of instinct existing in human genes, for e.g. I myself play video games every day, beyond the boundary of
    reality, I turn myself into romantic hero, which is extremely stress-free. Also, for the older adults, games
    bring them back to the innocence, entertain them at intervals of heavy work schedule, thus beneficial for their
    mental health. You know, sometimes I teach my parents how to play games, they appear to be pretty joyful when
    indulging themselves into games. For the seniors, playing games can especially help exercise their minds,
    prevent the degeneration of memory.-->

    <!--The person I'd like to talk with most is my friend Jennifer. she is really an excellent story teller.
